lessons.description:
The <kbd>position</kbd> property controls how elements are placed. <kbd>relative</kbd> keeps the element in normal flow but allows you to offset it with <kbd>top</kbd>, <kbd>right</kbd>, <kbd>bottom</kbd>, <kbd>left</kbd>.<br><br><pre>.box {
  position: relative;
  top: 10px;
}</pre>

Combine <kbd>position: absolute</kbd> with offset properties to place elements precisely.<br><br><pre>.close {
  position: absolute;
  top: 8px;
  right: 8px;
}</pre>
